    "location": "Local hair salon, Sheung Wan",
    "context": "Neighbourhood hair salons (髮廊) in Hong Kong are a social hub as much as a service. The stylist will chat throughout your cut — it's considered friendly. Be clear about what you want: length, style, fringe or no fringe.",
    "cultural_note": "Alongside modern salons, Hong Kong still has traditional 理髮廳 (lei5 faat3 teng1), old-style barbershops marked by the rotating red-white-blue pole. Some of these barbers have worked the same chair for forty years. The standard service includes a close shave, ear cleaning, and a scalp massage that feels like a medical procedure. A cut typically costs around HK$80, a fraction of a modern salon's price.",
